#. type: Yaml Front Matter Hash Value: title
#: content/community/_index.md:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Community"
msgstr "Communauté"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/community/_index.md:7
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Whether it be to solve a problem or to contribute in any way, the Xfce "
"communities are a good place to get help or to share your ideas. You might "
"also want to have a look at the communities of the different distributions "
"which provide Xfce.\n"
msgstr ""
"Qu’il s’agisse de résoudre un problème ou de collaborer, les communautés "
"Xfce sont un bon endroit pour trouver de l’aide ou partager vos idées. Il "
"peut aussi être intéressant de se rapprocher des communautés des "
"distributions qui embarquent Xfce.\n"

#. type: Title ##
#: content/community/_index.md:8
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Mailing lists"
msgstr "Listes de diffusion"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/community/_index.md:11
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Almost all development and coordination work is taking place on the Xfce "
"mailing lists. A summary of all lists is available at "
"[mail.xfce.org](https://mail.xfce.org). There is also a user-specific list "
"where you can ask questions and freely discuss about the desktop.\n"
msgstr ""
"Presque tout le travail de développement et de coordination se déroule sur "
"les listes de diffusions de Xfce que vous pourrez trouver à "
"[mail.xfce.org](https://mail.xfce.org). Il existe également une liste "
"spécifique où les utilisateurs peuvent poser leurs questions et discuter "
"librement du bureau.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/community/_index.md:13
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "**NOTE**: In order to post to these lists, you must first subscribe.\n"
msgstr ""
"** REMARQUE : ** Pour poster sur ces listes, vous devez d’abord vous "
"inscrire.\n"

#. type: Title ##
#: content/community/_index.md:14
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Matrix"
msgstr "Matrix"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/community/_index.md:17
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you have a problem that you cannot resolve, you might want to try asking "
"a question in our Matrix channel "
"[#xfce](https://matrix.to/#/#xfce:matrix.org). The channel has several "
"active users. It is recommended that you consult the "
"[documentation](https://docs.xfce.org/) about your problem before asking "
"your question.\n"
msgstr ""
"Si vous rencontrez un problème que vous ne parvenez pas à résoudre, vous "
"pouvez essayer de poser une question sur notre canal Matrix "
"[#xfce](https://matrix.to/#/#xfce:matrix.org). Ce canal compte plusieurs "
"utilisateurs actifs. Il est recommandé de consulter la "
"[documentation](https://docs.xfce.org/) relative à votre problème avant de "
"poser votre question.\n"

#. type: Title ##
#: content/community/_index.md:18
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Forums"
msgstr "Forums"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/community/_index.md:21
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"For users who prefer forums, the [Xfce Forum](https://forum.xfce.org/) is "
"the place to be. Active contributors will be able to help you, but please do"
" not use it for bug reports.\n"
msgstr ""
"Pour les utilisateurs qui préfèrent les forums, le [Forum "
"Xfce](https://forum.xfce.org/) est l’endroit idéal. Les contributeurs actifs"
" pourront vous aider, mais veuillez ne pas l’utiliser pour des rapports de "
"bogues.\n"

#. type: Title ##
#: content/community/_index.md:22
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Social Networks"
msgstr "Réseaux sociaux"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/community/_index.md:24
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You can follow us on the official [Mastodon "
"account](https://floss.social/@xfce) or [Twitter "
"account](https://twitter.com/xfceofficial)\n"
msgstr ""
"Vous pouvez nous suivre sur [le compte officiel "
"Mastodon](https://floss.social/@xfce) ou sur [le compte "
"Twitter](https://twitter.com/xfceofficial)\n"
